user

Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • user.User
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Observer

    public class User
extends java.lang.Object
implements Observer
    This class represents the users of the network. A User is created with a Username, and can have or not an initial position. Each User has a unique id and its own UserStat class that contains his statistics. A User can have an Ongoing Ride and can be following an Itinerary.
    Author:
    Chloé
    See Also:
    UserStat, UserIdGenerator
